guide.start.text: Welcome new PlantTechian. You are about to enter a world that combines plants and technology and pushes it to the limits. =nlResources are growable, plants are automatable and plant traits needs to be cultured. =nlAre you good enough to master the technology to use plants for your will? =nlFeel free to contact me for bugs or suggestions at =nltwitter.com/_Kaneka =nlminecraft.curseforge.com/projects/ planttech-2 =nlhttps://discord.gg/CUrahNz =nlHope you enjoy PlantTech 2
guide.plantium.text: A very important resource for your journey with PlantTech 2 is Plantium, a plant and metal hybrid resource. It is the basic material for creating almost everything in this mod. Metal on its own could not transfer the bioenergy as it is different to everything known.
guide.crops.text: Crops are a way of obtaining resources for your days in Minecraft but are a bit more complicated than vanilla crops. You start your journey with vanilla crops and crop bars; crossbreed to maximize the traits and unlock more and more types of crops. =nlFor the different types of plants and how to get them, just have a look in the plant encyclopedia.=nlOne feature of the crops is: right clicking on the fully-grown crop causes the crop to be replanted and spawns all the remaining drops in the world. =nlWhen obtaining new crop seeds, the traits are unknown. You can see them after putting the seeds in the identifier. =nlTo copy seeds, you just need to place crop bars next to a fully grown crop without other crops nearby.
guide.traits.text: Type: Describes the type of the plant. =nl =nlSoil: Crops only grows on this soil. =nl=nlGrow speed: The speed at which the plant grows; higher = faster=nl=nlSensitivity: Not implemented yet. =nl=nlLight level needed: Necessary light level for growth=nl=nlWater range: Distance from water that is necessary for growth=nl=nlTemperature: How tolerant the plant is to temperature=nl=nlProductivity: Affects the amount of non-seed drops. =nl=nlFertility: Increase the amount of seed drops. =nl=nlSpreading speed: Influence the time needed to spread over to next crop bars. =nl=nlGene strength: Not implemented yet. =nl=nlEnergy per seed: Affects the amount of energy produced in the seed squeezer. =nl
guide.crossbreeding.text: When there are blank crop bars between two fully-grown crops, crossbreeding happens. =nlThere is a small chance that the new crop is a new type. =nlFor the traits: if they are the same level, the new plant could have the traits with some additional. If they are different, the new crop trait is in-between the parent’s levels.  =nlThis way, you can maximize the traits and get the best crops possible.
guide.temperature.text: Every biome has its own temperature and every crop has its necessary temperature. =nlWith better traits you can develop a temperature tolerance. =nlTo get the temperature of the actual position, just use the thermometer.
guide.analyzer.text: When the crop isn’t growing, or you just need to know if everything is ok, you can use the analyzer on a crop. If there is any problem, you will be able to tell from the information given.
guide.machines.text: Seed squeezer: Extracts the bioenergy from seeds by pressing them. =nlByproduct:biomass every 16 seeds=nl =nlSolar Generator:  Produces bioenergy from sunlight. The better the solar focus, the higher the outcome. =nl =nlIdentifier: Used to identify the traits of the plant=nl =nlMega furnace: Electrical furnace with 6 slots. =nl =nlPlant farm: Automate the crop farming. =nl =nlCompressor: Compresses Particles into a mold to create resources.
guide.cables.text: Bioenergy needs to be transferred with cables. Every machine can be used as an energy consumer and/or energy supplier. Just use the wrench to toggle the connections. The arrow on the connection represents the flow direction of the energy.
guide.upgrades.text: There are two types of upgrades which can be used in the machines. =nl=nlSpeed upgrade: Increase the speed of the machine but also increases the energy costs. =nl =nlRange upgrade: Increase the range of the Plant Farm but also increases the energy costs.
guide.particles.text: Crops produce particles, which can be combined to obtain almost every resource in Minecraft. To combine the particles, you need to use the compressor and the right mold. =nlEvery crop produces the particles of its own type.
guide.genetic_engineering.text: It is possible to create seeds with unlocked traits with genetic engineering. =nlFor more information, get the Tablet: Genetic Engineering with the command =nl/planttech2 guide genetic
guide.armor.text: In PlantTech 2 there are several armors with special abilities that are bound to the armor type. You can enchant the armor as usual.=nl=nlDancium Armor: Waterbreeding =nl=nlKanekium Armor: Autorepair =nl=nlKinnoium Armor: Autofeed =nl=nlLenthurium Armor: Speedboost=nl=nlThe strength of the Effects depends on the amount of worn pieces of the set.
guide.ge_start.text: Genetic engineering is a way to create crops with selected traits. These traits need to be found first but could be used as much as you want. =nlSo, start crossbreed your crops and find traits you like to have.
guide.ge_extracting.text: Once you got traits you want to use, you need to extract the whole DNA sequence. =nlTherefore, put a seed with traits and an empty DNA container in the DNA extractor. You will obtain a DNA container with the whole DNA sequence; the seed will be destroyed in the process.
guide.ge_removing.text: Mostly you don’t want to use the whole DNA sequence. To remove single genes, put the DNA container in the DNA remover. =nlBut you can’t select which gene will be removed. =nlDon´t mess around when you only have a single container left. =nlOn this way you can reduce the genes up to one.
guide.ge_combining.text: DNA container can be combined in the DNA combiner. In this process the DNA sequences will be mixed, but the lower values will be dominant. =nlWhich type will be dominant is random.
guide.ge_cleaning.text: Not used Containers can be cleaned up to be reused in the DNA extractor. =nlTherefore, put the container in the DNA cleaner.
guide.ge_creating.text: Now the last step in getting personalized seeds is to put a DNA Container and 32 biomasses in the Seedconstructor. =nlBiomass Is a byproduct in the seedsqueezer.
